Master TODO list
================

This is a "compressed" list of things from 'alpha-checklist'.  For
gritty details about the problems and solutions, look there.

Meta-note:  we have defined M3 := "test suite and self-hosted".


* finish M2: get commit/import/update working over DAV (Greg)

* hunt down many memory bugs. (Chicago office)

* write test-suite (Chicago office)

* mulitple command-line targets.  (Chicago office)

* 'svn cp' and friends: cp, mv, branch, tag. (Ben will start)

* new 'libsvn_repos':  utils built on *top* of libsvn_fs

   * cross-process read/write lock function for DB_RUN_RECOVERY. (Greg)
   * hook system -- to fire off shell scripts.  (who?)
   * new location of fs commit-editor (Ben)
   * new location of delta_dirs and wrapper (Mike)
   * new location of shared 'reporter' code for both RA layers (Ben)

* Many filesystem improvements -- (Jim documents, Chicago implements)

   * deltified storage
   * strings table
   * real file streaming
   * dir_delta use 'copyfrom' args
   * keep node-rev-id strings short
   * copy properties

* misc subcommands:  svn cleanup, log, export, diff, rdiff, blame, merge,
                         revert, rollback, unadd, undel.  (Chicago office)

* autodetection of text/binary file types, and default boolean values
  for keyword substitution and newline translation. (Karl)

* change #6:  invert text-delta interface (Greg)

* simple Apache-only authentication & authorization (Greg)

* internalized diff/patch library:  (Ben will investigate)

* user documentation (Karl will research/look for volunteers)

* cvs2svn (Thom and Greg)

* UTF-8 preparations (Jim)

* general pool usage code-review (Greg and Fitz)

* wc improvement:  deal with removing files when dir is *not*
  up-to-date.  (Karl)

* change ra_local commit-style (Ben & Greg discuss)



